-- Turkey's Isbank says to issue up to 20 bln lira of borrowing instruments 
-- 
-- Thu Aug 28, 2014 11:03AM EDT
-- None



ISTANBUL, Aug 28 (Reuters) - Turkey's Isbank is looking to issue borrowing instruments worth up to 20 billion lira (9.27 billion) with varying maturities, the bank said on Thursday.

The statement was sent to the Istanbul Stock Exchange.